data.title: Calcium Intake and Lung Cancer Risk: A Pooled Analysis of 12 Prospective Cohort Studies
data.meta_description: In this largest prospective investigation, overall, calcium intake was not associated with risk of lung cancer, but milk intake was associated with a higher risk. Our findings underscore the importance of considering food sources of calcium in studies of calcium intake.
